<subSubSection id="C3126501D815FF9A3CB4FECB3089FAB8" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD815FF9A3CB4FECB3089FAB8" blockId="64.[151,1058,369,479]" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023">
D i a g n o s i s: The available member of this species is superficially similar to specimens of 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D815FF9A3D0FFE3433C1FAC5" box="[300,510,398,419]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023">
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D815FF9A3D0FFE34338FFAC5" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1834" box="[300,432,398,419]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platynoptera</taxonomicName>
similis
</emphasis>
OPITZ from which it differs by showing a narrow testaceous line between two broad black lines on the pronotal disc. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D815FF9A3CB4FE733324FAB8" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1834" box="[151,283,457,478]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D815FF9A3CB4FE733324FAB8" box="[151,283,457,478]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023">Platynoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
SPINOLA was revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B7BD815FF9A3E3FFE73308DFAB8" author="OPITZ W" box="[540,690,456,478]" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023" pagination="1513 - 1572" refId="ref53655" refString="OPITZ W. (2015 b): Systematics of the checkered beetle subfamily Platynopterinae SPINOLA (Coleoptera: Cleridae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 47 (2): 1513 - 1572." type="journal article" year="2015">OPITZ (2015b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126501D815FF9A3CB4FE5731C0F8F2" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD815FF9A3CB4FE5730FAF809" blockId="64.[151,1059,493,879]" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD815FF9A3E30FE57304AF964" box="[531,629,493,515]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023" unit="mm" value="11.5">11.5 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD815FF9A3EE8FE57311EF964" box="[715,801,493,515]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD815FF9A3FE1FE573623F965" box="[962,1052,493,515]" captionStart="Figs 354-357" captionStartId="116.[151,191,1512,1534]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,196,1487]" captionTargetId="figure@116.[153,1061,196,1495]" captionTargetPageId="116" captionText="Figs 354-357: Habitus; (354) Sirpa latiflava; (355) Topainca pachacutii; (356) Platynoptera potaro; (357) Artoadenus atrafinus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746840/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023">Fig. 357</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium bicolorous, clypeus and venter testaceous; frons and epicranium black except epicranium with narrow testaceous line at middle; antenna black; pronotal disc with two broad black vitta between which is narrow testaceous line, pronotal sides broadly testaceous, lower sides brown; pterothorax testaceous; elytra bicolorous, with broad testaceous marking extended posteriorly from humeral angle, with testaceous fascia at discal middle that expands from epipleural to sutural margin; legs mostly brown, basal 1/2 of femora testaceous; abdomen bicolorous, testaceous and brown. Head: Eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye slightly wider than frons (EW/FW 43/40); funicular antennomeres (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD815FF9A3DB9FD5333D8F999" box="[410,487,745,767]" captionStart="Figs 28-42" captionStartId="71.[151,191,1299,1321]" captionTargetBox="[152,1047,199,1264]" captionTargetId="figure@71.[152,1059,199,1284]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="Figs 28-42: Antennae; (28) Neorthopleura thomasi, male; (29) N. thomasi, female; (30) N. subfasciata, male; (31) Artoadenus atrafinus; (32) Neorthopleura subfasciata, female; (33) Akonesis atraordinis; (34) Pelonium erudiatum; (35) Neorthopleura cuspidis, female; (36) Agnatis curvabilis; (37) Ichnea paraguayensis; (38) Neorthopleura quintana, male; (39) Pyticara frontegalba; (40) Platynoptera potaro; (41) Neorthopleura cuspidis, male; (42) Nanoclerus fuscus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746748" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746748/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) transverse and very setose; capitular antennomeres 9 and 10 long rectangulate, antennomere 11 oblong ovate. Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD815FF9A3FE2FCBF3624F87D" box="[961,1051,773,795]" captionStart="Figs 163-170" captionStartId="79.[151,191,1521,1543]" captionTargetBox="[183,1039,199,1493]" captionTargetId="figure@79.[151,1059,199,1508]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="Figs 163-170: Pronota; (163) Artoadenus atrafinus; (164) Cregya triguttula; (165) C. biguttula; (166) Perilypus schusteri (167) Platynoptera potaro; (168) Pelonium erudiatum; (169) Parapelonides aodontus; (170) Isoparis cassidilis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746764/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023">Fig. 163</figureCitation>
) transverse; pronotal tubercles shallow (PW/PL 150/120), disc finely punctate; elytral asetiferous punctures minute and profusely distributed, elytra notably flared in posterior 1/2 (EL/EW 550/160). Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD815FF9A3CB4FCC531C0F8F2" blockId="64.[151,1023,894,916]" box="[151,1023,894,916]" pageId="64" pageNumber="1023">
